{"key":"processedPost-15460046","value":{"id":15460046,"first":15458551,"last":15460575,"when":1322956144,"utime":"12/04/11 01:49 AM","content":"The temperature on the AA75x is maintained by the thermostat.&nbsp; The mechanical timer only rings a bell, but does not shut the unit off.&nbsp; Once you bleed steam and shut the toggle valve, it becomes set and forget until it's time to shut off.&nbsp; Actually, I hate the term 'set and forget' because it implies you shouldn't monitor the unit during operation, which you should.&nbsp; Equipment fails and you should never leave it unattended.<br /><br />Don't expect to put 27 quart jars in the 75X.&nbsp; I think it holds 16 or something close to that, but I don't use jars any more..&nbsp; You can sterilize 27 quarts of grain, provided you use filter patch bags.<br /><br />You can also can in the 75X, but have to be there to release the toggle valve as soon as pressure reaches zero on cool down.&nbsp; I have 4 of them.&nbsp; You can get a cool cart to roll them on from U-line.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/11-005/701402201-AA-75X_on_cart.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/11-005/701402201-thumb_AA-75X_on_cart.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Sterilizer Questions","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}